<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--GirlKilled     12-16 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Girl Killed,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Girl Wrapping Christmas Presents Killed By Shotgun Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CENTRALIA, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old girl wrapping Christmas
presents was killed when her younger brother picked up a shotgun and
the weapon accidentally discharged, authorities said.
   Amorita I. Arias was wrapping the presents on a bed at their home
about 5:30 p.m. Thursday when her 7-year-old brother came into the
room and picked up the 12-gauge shotgun, said Lewis County Coroner
Terry Wilson.
   ``Whether he bumped it or actually pulled the trigger, I don't
know,'' Wilson said.
   The blast from 3 to 5 feet away killed the girl instantly.
   ``All the investigation that we've done proves that it was
accidental,'' Wilson said.
</TEXT>
