<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--TMIShutdown     12-16 0125</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--TMI Shutdown,0127</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the second time in four months, Three Mile
Island Unit 1 nuclear plant was scheduled for shutdown Thursday to
service one of four pumps that circulate water through the reactor
coolant system.
   The work is expected to be done in about 10 days, said Doug
Bedell, a spokesman for General Public Utilities Corp., which
operates TMI.
   The decision to shut down was made after plant operators
monitored a higher-than-normal water flow through one of three seals
around the pump shaft, Bedell said in a statement.
   The seal will be examined and any necessary corrective action
will be taken, he said.
   Unit 1 was shut down Sept. 17 for nine days for maintenance on
the same pump seal.
</TEXT>
