<1ST_LINE>r a PM-SubwayAttack     12-16 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Subway Attack,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Homeless Man Pushes Woman in Front of Subway Train</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homeless man who escaped from a mental
hospital six months ago pushed an elderly woman off a subway
platform into a train's path, critically injuring the woman, police
said.
   Edward Jones, 34, was chased and captured by an off-duty
Philadelphia police officer and a citizen after the attack Thursday,
said detective Capt. Michael Mongelluzzo.
   ``He pushed her off from the platform ... in front of a westbound
train for no apparent reason,'' Mongelluzzo said.
   The victim, Ruth Warrington, 63, was run over by the first four
cars of the subway train, suffering a fractured skull, broken pelvis
and knees, and massive blood loss, Mongelluzzo said.
   She was listed in critical and unstable condition at the Hospital
of the University of Pennsylvania, Mongelluzzo said.
   Jones was reported missing from the Philadelphia State Hospital
on June 22, Mongelluzzo said.
   ``He's a street person now. He's mentally deranged,'' he said.
   Jones was held on charges of aggravated and simple assault,
risking a catastrophe and recklessly endangering another person.
</TEXT>
