   Plate glass windows bowed at the Palm Springs police station and
rims around ceiling sprinkler heads fell to the floor, said Sgt. Ron
Starrs.
   ``I think it was the strongest one we had since the big one in
'86,'' Starrs said. He had no immediate report of serious damage or
injury.
   In neighboring Palm Desert, Mary Jo Lyon said the mirror on her
bedroom wall shook and she ran from the room to check on her
Christmas tree, which listed to one side after the jolt.
   ``It shook me up,'' she said.
   In Los Angeles, Chris Harris of Hollywood said his typewriter
fell off his desk, and pictures were askew following the quake.
