plans would have added a third floor to the house, which is at the
center of a 76-acre estate called Northview. North Castle zoning law
limits buildings to 2{ stories.
   Boesky paid a record $100 million fine in 1986 to settle federal
Securities and Exchange Commission charges of insider stock trading.
He is serving a three-year term after pleading guilty in April 1987
to a federal conspiracy charge, and will be eligible for parole in
March.
