<1ST_LINE>r a PM-TridentLaunch     12-16 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Trident Launch,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Navy Launches Trident 2 Missile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Trident 2 submarine missile today
logged its 13th success in 17 test launches, propelling a dummy
warhead package at an Atlantic Ocean target, the Navy reported.
   The three-stage, $23.7 million missile vaulted from a land launch
pad at 7:49 a.m. EST and darted southeast over the ocean. The Navy
reported 20 minutes after the launch that the test was a success.
   The 44-foot missile has a range of nearly 6,000 miles. Officials
would not say how far the warhead traveled today. Each Trident 2 is
capable of delivering 10 nuclear warheads to different targets.
   Three more test launches on land are planned before the Navy
begins test launchings from submarines.
   The missile is scheduled to become operational in about a year.
The Navy plans to install 24 Trident 2 missiles aboard each of nine
submarines.
</TEXT>
