<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The bodies of five Americans killed when
their locust-spraying plane was shot down by rebels have been handed
over to the U.S Embassy, government and U.S. officials said today.
   About 100 personal items of the five were handed over at a
ceremony Thursday, the officials said.
   The bodies were brought to the embassy by a Polisario Red Cross
unit. Polisario, the movement fighting Morocco for independence of
the former Spanish territory of Western Sahara, admitted it mistook
the U.S. plane for a Moroccan military jet and shot it down.
   The DC-7 was hit by a ground-to-air missile halfway between the
Mauritanian border and the defensive perimeter Morocco built against
the Polisario rebels.
