<HEAD>Bomb Blast Damages Nightclub In Nicosia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A popular Nicosia nightclub was bombed for
the second time in four months Friday in what police believe is a
business feud.
   A police statement said there were no casualties in the predawn
blast at the Pavilion which occurred two hours after the club had
closed for the night.
   The first bombing Aug. 8 caused extensive damage. The club
reopened a few weeks ago. Police gave no other details on the blast
Friday or the feud.
</TEXT>
