<2ND_LINE>AM-Philippines-Cardinal,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cardinal, Two Priests Attacked During Mass</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CEBU CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Roman Catholic cardinal of Cebu
and two other priests were attacked and beaten Saturday by a man as
they were giving communion at an early morning Mass, police said.
   Police and witnesses said the man, Eduardo Espinosa, struck
Cardinal Ricardo Vidal, 57, with his fist in the back of the neck,
sending him sprawling to the floor.
   Two other priests, Rev. Achilles Dakay and Rev. Hermingildo
Montecillo, rushed to the cardinal's aid and were also beaten,
police said.
   The incident occurred during early morning services at a church
in Talisay, 7 miles south of Cebu City.
   Vidal was rushed to a hospital and was reported resting. The
assailant was arrested. Patrolman Hannibal Larida said the man told
police he was ``out of my mind'' when he attacked the cardinal.
  
</TEXT>
