<HEAD>Rates on 52-Week Bills Hit 3{-Year High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills rose
in the latest auction to the highest level in 3{ years.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.0 billion of the bills Thursday
at an average discount rate of 8.49 percent, up from 7.92 percent at
the last auction on Nov. 17.
   The rates were the highest since March 14, 1985, when the
one-year bills sold for 9.24 percent. The new discount rate
understates the actual return to investors _ 9.20 percent with a
$10,000 bill selling for $9,141.60.
