<HEAD>Crystal Brands Acquires Palm Beach for $300 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOUTHPORT, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crystal Brands Inc. has announced the
acquisition of rival clothing manufacturer Palm Beach Inc. for $300
million.
   Under the deal announced Thursday, Crystal Brands will refinance
Palm Beach's $205 million debt.
   Crystal Brands acquired the company from an investment group led
by Merrill Lynch Capital Partners that had taken Palm Beach private
through a leveraged buyout in 1985.
   In 1987, Cincinnati-based Palm Beach reported sales of $404
million. Crystal Brands had sales of $360 million the same year.
   ``The addition of Palm Beach will expand dramatically our current
base in apparel,'' said Richard F. Kral, chairman and chief
executive officer of Crystal Brands. ``It will broaden our product
categories to include tailored clothing, formal wear and dress
furnishings as well as extend our current base in sportswear.''
   With the addition of Palm Beach, Crystal Brands will produce
sportswear under the Izod and Lacoste brand names and clothing under
the following brand names: Palm Beach, Evan Picone, Gant, Haspel,
John Weitz, Eagle Shirtmakers, Calvin Clothing, Polo by Ralph Lauren
for Boys and Pierre Cardin for Boys.
