<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     12-16 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0214</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Up at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were higher near the day's peak at
midday Friday on British economic figures which have buoyed the
market's mood.
   Dealers said share prices continued to advance on the growing
belief that the British government won't have to increase interest
rates further to slow down inflationary pressures on the British
economy.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 9.3
points, or 0.5 percent, at 1,772.5 at about 12:45 p.m., near the
morning peak of 9.9 points up.
   Volume was a moderate 235.8 million shares compared with 228.7
million shares at the same time Thursday.
   Dealers said the market has been gradually shaking off its
previous concerns about the effects of high interest rates on
British corporate profitability. Until recently, many analysts
thought the government would have to push base lending rates above
the current 13 percent level to slow down the British economy and
choke off inflation.
   But recent economic figures, especially average earnings figures
released Thursday and retail sales figures published last Monday,
have suggested the economy is already responding to higher rates.
   On Friday, the government reported that the annual rate of
inflation held steady at 6.4 percent in November.
</TEXT>
