<HEAD>Toyota Aviation Unit to Market Cessnas in China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The California-based aviation unit of Toyota Motor
Sales U.S.A. Inc. will export and market Cessna aircraft to the
People's Republic of China, the company says.
   In a news release from Torrance, Calif., Toyota Aviation U.S.A.
Inc. said it will sell and maintain the Caravan I and II turboprop
airplanes in China through Toyota Tsusho Corp., which has offices in
China and Hong Kong.
